'''Mehdi Ghayedi''' ({{langx|fa|مهدی قایدی}}; born 5 December 1998) is an Iranian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Winger (soccer)|winger]] or [[Forward (association football)|second striker]] for [[UAE Pro League]] club [[Al-Nasr SC (Dubai)|Al-Nasr]] and the [[Iran national football team|Iran national team]].

==Club career==

===Iranjavan Bushehr===
Ghayedi was born in [[Bushehr]] and began his career at the youth level with local side [[F.C. Iranjavan Bushehr|Iranjavan Bushehr]].<ref name="Bio">{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1420798/آشنایی-با-باشو-غریبه%E2%80%8Cی-کوچک-آبی%E2%80%8Cهای-تهران|script-title=fa:آشنایی با باشو غریبه‌ی کوچک (المهدی گاییدی)آبی‌های تهران|language=fa}}</ref> After his promotion to the senior squad, he was named the 2016–17 [[Azadegan League]] Young Player of the Season for scoring 10 league goals.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://90tv.ir/video/408456/مهدی-قائدی-پدیده-لیگ-یک-در-فصل-95-96|title=مهدی قائدی، پدیده لیگ یک در فصل ۹۵-۹۶ |language=fa<!-- script-title doesn't work well here -->}}</ref>

===Esteghlal===
[[File:Mehdi Ghaedi.jpg|thumb|left|150px|Ghayedi playing for [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]] in 2017]]
On 8 June 2017, Ghayedi signed a three-year contract with [[Esteghlal F.C.|Esteghlal]].<ref>{{cite web|script-title=fa:قائدی رسما استقلالی شد|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1420755|language=fa}}</ref> Upon signing, he was given the number 16.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=fa:عجیب ترین پیراهن استقلال بر تن پژمان منتظری|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1452099/عجیب-ترین-پیراهن-استقلال-بر-تن-پژمان-منتظری|language=fa}}</ref>

At the start of the 2017–18 season, the [[Football Federation Islamic Republic of Iran|FFIRI]] barred Ghayedi from playing for Esteghlal, along with club teammates [[Majid Hosseini]] and [[Omid Noorafkan]], as the three were expected to join the Iran under-23 training camp.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1428874/محرومیت-3-بازیکن-استقلال-از-هفته-اول-لیگ!|title=محرومیت 3 بازیکن استقلال از هفته اول لیگ|language=fa<!-- script-title doesn't work well here -->}}</ref> However, the order was cancelled on 29 July 2017, with Ghayedi missing only the first week of the new season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1450468/محرومیت-سه-بازیکن-استقلال-لغو-شد|script-title=fa:محرومیت سه بازیکن استقلال لغو شد|language=fa}}</ref> He made his debut for Esteghlal as a substitute on 4 August 2017 in a 0–0 draw against [[Esteghlal Khuzestan F.C.|Esteghlal Khuzestan]], becoming the youngest league player to ever play for the club.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1451851/استقلال-0-اس-خوزستان-0؛-آبی%E2%80%8Cها-شاکی-از-داور-و-دیوار|title=استقلال 0 - استقلال خوزستان 0؛ آبی‌ها شاکی از داور و دیوار|language=fa<!-- script-title doesn't work well here -->}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |date=6 August 2017 |script-title=fa:قائدی رکورد جوان‌ترین بازیکن تاریخ استقلال را در لیگ برتر شکست |url=http://www.isna.ir/news/96051509034/قائدی-رکورد-جوان-ترین-بازیکن-تاریخ-استقلال-را-در-لیگ-برتر-شکست |language=fa}}</ref> Despite limited minutes, Ghayedi was praised on his debut for his skills and effort.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1452031/نیمار-در-آزادی،-نه-در-پاریس!|script-title=fa:نیمار در آزادی، نه در پاریس!|language=fa}}</ref>

Ghayedi made his first start for the club in a 3–0 victory over Sepahan on 6 December 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.tarafdari.com/خبر/858892/استقلال-3-0-سپاهان؛-در-روز-سوپر-گل-ها،-طلسم-های-استقلال-شکسته-شد|title=استقلال 3-0 سپاهان؛ در روز سوپر گل ها، طلسم های استقلال شکسته شد|date=11 August 2017|language=fa}}</ref> On 25 January 2018, he was named [[Player of the match|man of the match]] for his performance in a 4–0 victory against [[F.C. Pars Jonoubi Jam|Pars Jonoubi Jam]], during which he provided an [[Assist (association football)|assist]] and won a [[Penalty kick (association football)|penalty kick]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1500173/گزارش-بازی-استقلال-تهران-پارس-جنوبی-05-11-96|title=استقلال 4- پارس جم 0؛ خط آتش آبی فاتح روز جنجالی |trans-title=Esteghlal 4 Pars Jam 0;|publisher=Varzesh3.com|language=fa|date=30 January 2018 |accessdate=3 February 2018<!-- script-title doesn't work well here -->}}</ref>

On 29 January 2018, Ghayedi was involved in a serious car crash in his hometown of Bushehr, along with friends and a cousin, who died a few days later.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1501151/تصادف-شدید-خودروی-ستاره-جوان-استقلال-عکس|script-title=fa:آخرین اخبار از وضعیت مهدی قائدی بعد از تصادف |trans-title=Latest news on Mehdi Ghaedi after the accident|publisher=Varzesh3.com|language=fa|date=29 January 2018 |accessdate=2 February 2018}}</ref> As a result of the accident, Ghayedi required surgery on his [[spleen]] and was ruled out for the rest of the season.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1501160/آخرین-وضعیت-روند-درمان-و-آسیب-دیدگی-قائدی|script-title=fa:آخرین وضعیت روند درمان و آسیب دیدگی قائدی |trans-title=Mehdi Ghaedi's latest injury and therapy situation|publisher=Varzesh3.com|language=fa|date=29 January 2018 |accessdate=2 February 2018}}</ref> A day later, Esteghlal beat [[Sanat Naft Abadan F.C.|Sanat Naft]] in [[2017–18 Hazfi Cup#Sixth Round (Semi-Final)|Hazfi Cup]], and Ghayedi's teammates dedicated the victory to him.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1501520/خوشحالی-شجاعیان-با-پیراهن-مهدی-قائدی|script-title=fa:خوشحالی شجاعیان با پیراهن مهدی قائدی |trans-title=Shojaeian's celebration with Mehdi Ghay edi's shirt.|publisher=Varzesh3.com|language=fa|date=30 January 2018 |accessdate=2 February 2018}}</ref>

===Shabab Al Ahli===
During the summer of 2021, Ghayedi was heavily linked with a move to [[Qatar Stars League|Qatari]] side [[Al-Gharafa SC|Al-Gharafa]].<ref>{{cite web |script-title=fa:لاعب الاستقلال الإيراني مهدي قايدي في طريقه إلى الغرافة |url=https://staddoha.com/اخبار/الاخبار-المحلية/أخبار-كرة-القدم/لاعب-الاستقلال-الإيراني-مهدي-قايدي-في/ |website=استاد الدوحة |language=ar |date=13 August 2021}}</ref> However on 23 August 2021, he signed for [[UAE Pro League|Emerati]] side [[Shabab Al Ahli Club|Shabab Al Ahli]] on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=AlBayanSports|number=1429789746771992577|script-title=fa:شركة نادي شباب الأهلي لكرة القدم، تتعاقد مع اللاعب الدولي الإيراني مهدي قائدي "22 سنة" لمدة 5 مواسم، تدعيماً لصفوف الفريق الأول للمرحلة المقبلة|date=23 August 2021|language=ar}}</ref>

==International career==

===Youth===
Ghayedi was selected by manager [[Amir Hossein Peiravani]] to join the [[Iran national under-20 football team|Iran under-20]] team for the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup]]. After sitting on the bench for Iran's opening match against [[Costa Rica national under-20 football team|Costa Rica]], Ghayedi made his tournament debut against [[Zambia national under-20 football team|Zambia]], playing for 18 minutes in Iran's 4–2 defeat.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1417753/ایران-2-زامبیا-4-؛-توفان-آفریقایی-در-10-دقیقه|title=ایران 2 - زامبیا 4 ؛ توفان آفریقایی در 10 دقیقه |language=fa<!-- script-title doesn't work well here -->}}</ref> He also played for a few minutes against [[Portugal national under-20 football team|Portugal]] as Iran lost the match and was knocked out of the competition.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.varzesh3.com/news/1418308/ایران-1-پرتغال-2؛-با-دو-ویدئو-چک-حذف-شدیم|title=ایران 1- پرتغال 2؛ با دو ویدئو چک حذف شدیم|language=fa<!-- script-title doesn't work well here -->}}</ref>

===Senior===
[[File:Hong Kong v Iran (17) (cropped).jpg|thumb|213x213px|Ghayedi with [[Iran national football team|Iran]] at the [[2023 AFC Asian Cup]]]]
On 8 October 2020, Ghayedi made his senior international debut in a [[Exhibition game|friendly]] against [[Uzbekistan national football team|Uzbekistan]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2020-10-08 |title=Uzbekistan vs. Iran 1 - 2 |url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2020/10/08/world/friendlies/uzbekistan/iran/3287333/ |access-date=2020-10-09 |website=soccerway.com}}</ref>

==Style of play==
Ghayedi often uses [[Nutmeg (association football)|nutmeg]] skill for dribbling in one-on-one situations. He is also known for his use of long range shots.<ref>{{cite web |script-title=fa:گل اول استقلال به پرسپولیس توسط قایدی |url=https://video.varzesh3.com/video/219343/گل-اول-استقلال-به-پرسپولیس-توسط-قایدی/ |website=ویدیو ورزش سه |date=26 August 2020 |language=fa}}</ref>

==Personal life==

=== Political views ===
On 24 January 2026, Ghayedi shared on Instagram a poem by the 11th-century Persian poet [[Ferdowsi]], "Surely, come to mourn with us... from the sight of the blood that has fallen to the earth." He did so in reaction to a video from the [[2025–2026 Iranian protests]] showing a father in [[Kahrizak]] searching for the body of his son, who was [[2026 Iran massacres|killed by regime forces]].<ref>https://www.iranintl.com/202601244057</ref> On 31 January, rumors began circulating that Ghayedi would withdraw from the national team in response to the government's suppression of the protests; however, the [[Football Federation of the Islamic Republic of Mauritania|FFRI]] dismissed the claims as false.<ref>https://www.iranintl.com/202601310090</ref>

